componentType.name: Process
componentType.description:
A Process is a series of operations that transforms Input into Output by use of certain Mechanisms under the Control of some external system or higher-level Processes.

A Process takes up a certain interval in the information space, defined by a start action and close action. Actions are events or subprocesses. The internals of a Process may be broken down into subprocesses in a recursive manner. A Process is named by a verb or verb phrase.

propertyDefinition.name: Prefix
propertyDefinition.description:
The first part of the Identification, e.g. Node A3.2.1, here 'Node A' is the prefix. This property will automatically propagate to parts.

If you enter a Prefix on a part, a new numbering scheme will start there.

propertyDefinition.name: Punctuation Mark
propertyDefinition.description: The character(s) separating the numbers in the Identification, e.g. Node A3.2.1, here '.' is the punctuation mark. This property will automatically propagate to parts.

propertyDefinition.name: Sequence Number
propertyDefinition.description: The sequence number of a subprocess relative to its parent, e.g. Node A3.2.1, here '1' is the sequence number of the current process.

relationshipType.name: Sequence Flow
relationshipType.description: A sequence flow is used to show the order that activities will be performed in a process. Sequence flows have a Name attribute which will be shown on the flow, and they have a Kind attribute that can be used to specify whether the sequence flow is a conditional flow (mini-diamond) or a default flow (special marker on symbol). Default flows are typically used for one out of several possible outputs from gateway object. Conditional flows are typically starting directly on a process (and not on a gateway).
